      "content": "The candles have all burned down to nothing but wax and ash, much like my heart. He is gone... he has betrayed every vow, every whispered promise under the willow trees. There is no light left in this wretched world for me, only a heavy, suffocating darkness. I feel as though I am already a ghost, just waiting for my body to catch up to the hollowness within. It would all be so much quieter if I could just... simply fade away.",
